<p style="text-align: left;">
 
<span style="font-size: 25px;"><strong>c. 1940s &#8211; Idlewild Lodge News</strong></span>


<br>
An issue of Idle Wild News made by then grade schooler Leslie Ann Dauth.

<br>
<br>
<span style="font-size: 20px;"><i><strong>Transcription</strong></i></span> 

<br>
<span style="font-size: 22px;"><i>IDLE WILD NEWS</i></span> 


<br>
<i>"Edited By Leslie Ann Dauth; NEWS, Mrs. Dauth’s Back, Mrs. George Dauth is back from a trip to Yellow Stone Park with Mr. and Mrs. Jones June, 13; Accitentes [Accidents] While horse back riding Mr. Bill Lange bumped into a telephone pole and dented his bumper; Horse Back riding, Miss Elizabeth Ann Becker and Mr. Bill Lang went horse back riding to Deserted Village.; Trips, Elizabeth Ann Becker took a trip to Estes Park and got her pitcure [picture] drawn and framend [framed]; Hiking, Elizabeth Ann Becker, Bill Lang, and Jerry and Leslie Ann Dauth took their lunch and hiked up to Lookout mountain.; Games Mr. Lang from Kanses [Kansas] City is getting to be very good at suffelboard [shuffle board]. Starting at a low score to a high score of 207; Weather, Cooler today and tomorrow, High 88 Low 78"</i>


<br><br>
<span style="font-size: 20px;"><i><strong>People</strong></i></span> 
<br>






Leslie Ann Dauth


<br>





Florence Dauth


<br>





Bill Lang


<br>





Elizabeth Ann Becker


<br>





Jerry Dauth


<br>





<br>
<span style="font-size: 20px;"><i><strong>Details</strong></i></span> 


<br>
<i>Date: c. 1940s</i>


<br>
<i>Location: USA, Colorado, Loveland, Idlewild</i>




<br>
<i>Source: Dauth Family Archive</i>


<br>


<i>Permalink:</i>
<a href="https://www.idlewildlodge.org/document/c-1940s-idlewild-lodge-news/">https://www.idlewildlodge.org/document/c-1940s-idlewild-lodge-news/</a>



</p>
